cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.CE 

This paper deals with the problem of influence maximization in a network, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of social networks (cs.SOC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE). Additionally, the paper proposes two new metrics for influence maximization, which involves analyzing the performance of nodes in a network, and this falls under the sub-category of social influence (cs.SI).
